                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north base of the central shrine in the Madyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga. Year 11.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The inscription may palæographically be assigned to the 12th century A.D. It records the construction of a gateway, two steps and a door in the <hi rend="italic">ardhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the temple of Tirunāgīśuram-uḍaiya Nāyaṉār by Tiruchchiṟṟambala-kōṉ, son of <hi rend="italic">manṟāḍi</hi> Kaṟaḍi Ūraṉ. </p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
